transcript.text: Welcome to own Print Shop.
In this video, we'll explore the latest enhancements to the Studio features.
Let's walk through each improvement step by step.
First, we're excited to announce an upgrade to the QR Code feature in the Designer Studio.
Previously, QR code settings were located under the My Account section, but to make the process more intuitive and design friendly, we've moved this functionality directly into the Designer Studio.
Now, customers can easily create and customize QR codes right within their design workflow.
To use the new feature, simply open the Designer Studio and click on Add QR Code.
From there, you can select the type of QR you want to generate, such as a URL, e-mail, or contact information.
You can further personalize the QR code by clicking on the Style tab, where you can modify the QRS dot shapes, eye patterns, and choose from a range of colors and backgrounds.
There's also an option to add a logo at the center of the QR code for a more professional and branded appearance.
Once you've customized your QR code, simply hit Save and apply and you'll be able to place it directly onto your design.
Next, we've introduced a new enhancement to make working with templates even smoother.
Automatic translation of template text during the Browse Design flow.

Now, when a user selects a template, the text will be automatically translated after the template loads in the Designer Studio, with a loading indicator displayed during the process to ensure a seamless experience.
To control this behavior, a new new setting has been added under Studio Settings.
Admins can enable or disable this automatic translation feature based on their stores requirements, offering flexibility for multilingual storefronts.
Another powerful enhancement is the new Convert Raster to Vector feature.
With just a click, users can now convert raster images such as Jpegs or PNGS into Scalable Vector Graphics VG.
This conversion ensures sharper, pixel free output when resizing artwork and makes it much easier to edit logos, illustrations, and other graphics that require high precision for print.
To make template personalization even more flexible, we've introduced automatic resizing of design elements based on the products dimensions while preserving their original aspect ratio.
This enhancement ensures that templates can be easily reused across different product sizes without the need for manual adjustments.
To enable this functionality, a new setting called Resize Personalized Template has been added in Designer Studio, giving admins full control over how templates adapt during personalization.
Finally, we've expanded design flexibility by introducing the Small Caps Font Style Small Caps for PDF blocks.

This edition allows customers to apply a professional looking small caps effect to headings, product names, branding elements, and disclaimers, boosting both the readability and the visual impact of printed designs.
These studio enhancements are designed to simplify the design process, improve efficiency, and deliver a more polished output.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chatononprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
